defs.name: InvalidValue
defs.docs:
Error returned a value for a given directive is invalid.
 This can also happen when the value is missing, if the directive requires a value.

defs.name: InvalidOptionValue
defs.docs:
Error returned when a value for a given option is invalid.
 This can also happen when the value is missing, if the option requires a value.

defs.docs: Error returned when a invalid option is found.

defs.name: InvalidDirective
defs.docs: Error returned when a invalid directive is found.

defs.name: InvalidIp
defs.docs: Error returned when a value cannot be parsed an an IP address.

defs.name: ExtraData

defs.name: Config
defs.value: Config { nameservers, sortlist, debug, ndots, timeout, attempts, rotate, no_check_names, inet6, ip6_bytestring, ip6_dotint, edns0, single_request, single_request_reopen, no_tld_query, use_vc, lookup, family }
defs.docs:
Represent a resolver configuration, as described in `man 5 resolv.conf`.
 The options and defaults match those in the linux `man` page.

defs.name: nameservers
defs.docs: List of nameservers

defs.name: sortlist
defs.docs: List of preferred addresses

defs.name: debug
defs.docs: Enable DNS resolve debugging

defs.name: ndots
defs.docs: Number of dots in name to try absolute resolving first (default 1)

defs.name: timeout
defs.docs: Dns query timeout (default 5 [sec])

defs.name: attempts
defs.docs: Number of attempts to resolve name if server is inaccesible (default 2)

defs.name: rotate
defs.docs: Round-robin selection of servers (default false)

defs.name: no_check_names
defs.docs: Don't check names for validity (default false)

defs.name: inet6
defs.docs: Try AAAA query before A

defs.name: ip6_bytestring
defs.docs:
Use reverse lookup of ipv6 using bit-label format described instead
 of nibble format

defs.name: ip6_dotint
defs.docs:
Do ipv6 reverse lookups in ip6.int zone instead of ip6.arpa
 (default false)

defs.name: edns0
defs.docs: Enable dns extensions described in RFC 2671

defs.name: single_request
defs.docs: Don't make ipv4 and ipv6 requests simultaneously

defs.name: single_request_reopen
defs.docs: Use same socket for the A and AAAA requests

defs.name: no_tld_query
defs.docs: Don't resolve unqualified name as top level domain

defs.name: use_vc
defs.docs: Force using TCP for DNS resolution

defs.name: lookup
defs.docs:
The order in which databases should be searched during a lookup
 **(openbsd-only)**

defs.name: family
defs.docs:
The order in which internet protocol families should be prefered
 **(openbsd-only)**
